# No push without approval

**Never run `git push` (to any remote or branch) unless the user explicitly asks you to push in that conversation.**

Pushing to GitHub deploys to Vercel for this project — treat push as a production action.

## Required workflow

1. Make and test changes locally (e.g. `localhost:3000`, Studio) when possible.
2. **Commit only when the user asks** (existing git safety rules still apply).
3. **Stop before push** and tell the user what will go live.
4. Push **only** after clear approval, e.g. “push it”, “deploy to production”, “push to main”.

## Do not push when the user says

- “commit” (without also asking to push)
- “looks good” / “thanks” / “yes please” to a **feature** request (unless they clearly mean push/deploy)
- “revert on live site” — confirm, commit if needed, then **ask again** before pushing unless they explicitly included push/deploy in the same message

## When blocked from pushing

Say briefly that changes are committed locally (if applicable) and ready to push when they approve.

## Allowed without push approval

- `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, local commits (if requested), local dev server, local builds/tests
